-- Taiwan Equity Movers: MediaTek Inc., Motech Industries
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-13T06:11:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/taiwan-equity-movers-foxconn-technology-president-chain-store.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.6 percent to 7,912.91, the highest
since Aug. 4.  MediaTek Inc. (2454)  (2454 TT) jumped 6.9 percent to NT$311.50,
the highest close since Nov. 15. The chip designer may win
clients after showcasing a new product at the  Mobile World
Congress , the Economic Daily News reported, citing market
speculation. David Ku, spokesman for MediaTek, wasn’t
immediately available for comment.  Motech Industries Inc. (6244)  (6244 TT) retreated 4.9 percent to
NT$63.70, the biggest decline since Dec. 15. The solar cell-
maker declined to comment in a statement to the Taiwan stock
exchange on an Economic Daily News report today that a director,
Lee Ching-ming, was investigated for alleged  insider trading .
Operations at the company aren’t affected, according to the
statement. Lee wasn’t available to take calls made today to
Motech headquarters in Tainan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
